{{Italic title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{About|the television series|other Seven Wonders|Wonders of the World (disambiguation)}} {{refimprove|date=June 2018}} '''''Seven Natural Wonders''''' was a [[television series]] that was broadcast on [[BBC Two]] from 3 May to 20 June 2005. The programme took an area of England each week and, from votes by the people living in that area, showed the 'seven natural wonders' of that area in a programme.
The programmes were:
{| class="wikitable" |- !Rank!!Area!!Date!!Presenter!!Seven wonders covered |- |1||South West||3 May||[[Samantha Smith (TV presenter)|Samantha Smith]]||[[Dartmoor]], [[Jurassic Coast]], [[St Michael's Mount]], [[Exmoor]], [[Isles of Scilly]], [[The Lizard]], [[Newquay]] Coast |- |2||Yorkshire & Lincolnshire||9 May||[[Paul Hudson]]||[[Malham Cove]], the [[Yorkshire Three Peaks|Three Peaks]], [[Flamborough Head]], [[Hornsea Mere]], [[The Wash]], [[Thorne and Hatfield Moors]], [[Spurn Head]] |- |3||London||16 May||[[Bill Oddie]]||[[Islands in the River Thames]], the [[London Plane]], City Gardens, [[Hampstead Heath]], [[WWT London Wetlands Centre|London Wetland Centre]], [[Epping Forest]], [[Chislehurst Caves]]. |- |4||The North||23 May||[[Chris Jackson (TV presenter)|Chris Jackson]]||[[Lake District]], [[River Wear]], [[Whin Sill]], [[Aysgarth Falls]], [[River Tees]], [[Lindisfarne|Holy Island]], [[Morecambe Bay]] |- |5||The South||30 May||[[Aubrey Manning]]||[[The Needles]], [[Lulworth Cove]], [[Devil's Punch Bowl]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/england/sevenwonders/south/devils_punchbowl/|title=BBC: Seven Man Made Wonders|accessdate=20 June 2018}}</ref> [[The Ridgeway]], [[Stokenchurch Gap]], [[Finchampstead Ridges]], [[Cuckmere Haven]] |- |6||The Midlands||6 June||[[Dominic Heale]]||[[Kinder Scout]], [[Dovedale]], [[Blue John Cavern]], [[Creswell Crags]], [[Sherwood Forest]], [[Beacon Hill, Leicestershire|Beacon Hill]], [[Wenlock Edge]] |- |7||The West Country||17 June||[[Amanda Parr]]||[[Avebury]], [[Symonds Yat]], [[Cheddar Gorge]], [[Roman Baths (Bath)|Bath Hot Springs]], [[River Severn]], [[Glastonbury Tor]], [[Exmoor]] |- |8||South East||22 June||[[Kaddy Lee-Preston]]||[[White Cliffs of Dover]], [[Seven Sisters, Sussex|Seven Sisters]], [[North Downs]], [[Dungeness (headland)|Dungeness]], [[Romney Marsh]], [[Ecclesbourne]] [[Glen]], [[Pegwell Bay]] |}
The series covered eight regions of England, having originated as a 'local' television project.
There was also a series, looking at a similar selection of 'man-made' wonders for each of eleven regions of England.
